modules.description: This module executes OCaml code strings in a JavaScript runtime, providing `use` and `execute` functions to evaluate code with configurable output. It works with string inputs representing OCaml code and uses formatters for output control. Useful for embedding an OCaml interpreter in web applications or running dynamically generated OCaml code client-side.

This module evaluates OCaml code strings in a JavaScript environment using `use` and `execute`, directing output through specified formatters. It operates on string-based OCaml source and supports dynamic code execution. Ideal for embedding an OCaml interpreter in web apps or processing generated OCaml code client-side.
